The President of the United States has issued a statement welcoming the decision by the United Kingdom to join the coalition partners in striking ISIL targets in Syria. The President emphasizes the strong relationship between the US and the UK and expresses gratitude for the UK's support in fighting ISIL. The President also commends Germany for committing up to 1,200 troops to support coalition efforts against ISIL, pending parliamentary approval. The President emphasizes the need for a global response to defeat ISIL and welcomes any genuine counter-ISIL efforts by partners. The President looks forward to working closely with the UK, Germany, and all coalition partners to degrade and destroy ISIL.